# Image-Genetics Regression Pipeline

This repository contains a **fully automated OLS regression pipeline** to test **SNP × subtype interactions** on **resting-state connectivity features**, adjusting for common covariates (age, sex, scanner, scan_type).

It is a structured, GitHub-ready refactor of the **first three cells** of your notebook.

## Quick start (single command)

1) Put your input CSV files into the `data/` folder (see required filenames below).  
2) Run:

```bash
bash run.sh
```

That one command will:
- create a local virtual environment in `.venv/`
- install all required dependencies
- run the pipeline
- write outputs into `outputs/`

## Required input files (place these in `data/`)

- `genotype_matrix.csv`
- `Connectivity_matrix_all_subjects_region_pairs.csv`
- `subject_covariates.csv`
- `snp_metadata.csv`

### Expected key columns

- All datasets must have a subject identifier column that can be harmonized to `Subject_ID`
  - supported variants: `Subject_ID`, `Subject ID`, `subject_id`, `SubjectId`
- `subject_covariates.csv` must include:
  - `age`, `sex`, `scanner`, `scan_type`
  - `Subtype` **or** `group` (it will be renamed to `Subtype`)
- `snp_metadata.csv` must include:
  - `SNP` (rsID, e.g., `rs12345`)
  - `Case`, `Control` (subtype names)

## Outputs

Written to `outputs/` (default):

- `all_regression_result.csv`
- `all_regression_result_FDR.csv`
- `significant_result.csv`

## Custom run (optional)

```bash
source .venv/bin/activate
python -m imggenetics --data-dir data --output-dir outputs --subject-to-exclude 029_S_2395
```

Run `python -m imggenetics --help` to see all options.
